feat(api): :sparkles: add per-IP rate limiting middleware

Why:
The API lacks protection against abuse and has no request rate limits.
A single client can make unlimited requests, potentially causing service
degradation for all users and exhausting server resources.

What:
Implement sliding window rate limiter middleware using Redis backend.
Configurable per-IP with default 100 requests per 15-minute window.
Returns 429 Too Many Requests with Retry-After header when exceeded.

Ticket: PROJ-312
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
